## Architecture notes

- Web talks to Application services (no DbContext in controllers)
- Application depends on Domain abstractions and raises events via IEventBus
- Web adapts IEventBus to Swap.Htmx, maps domain events to `ui.*` via chains
- UI listens via HTMX `hx-trigger` and swaps only the content area

In `Web/Program.cs` (excerpt):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSwapHtmx(events =>
{
	events.Chain(
		SwapEvents.Entity.Created("todo"),
		SwapEvents.UI.RefreshList,
		SwapEvents.UI.ShowToast);
});
```

A view:

```html
<div id="todo-list"
	 hx-get="/Home/TodoList"
	 hx-trigger="load, ui.refreshList from:body"
	 hx-swap="outerHTML"></div>
```

Dev endpoints (Development only): `/_swap/dev/events` shows active chains and emissions.

## Run it locally

From `src/Web/`:

```bash
npm install
libman restore
npm run build:css
```

From the solution root:

```bash
# Create DB (CLI usually does this for you)
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate -p src/Infrastructure -s src/Web
dotnet ef database update -p src/Infrastructure -s src/Web

# Run the web app
cd src/Web
dotnet run
```

Open http://localhost:5000

Tip: `npm run watch:css` from `src/Web` will rebuild CSS during development.

## Testing with Swap.Testing

Integration tests live under `test/Integration` and use the `HtmxTestFixture<TProgram>` and `HtmxTestClient<TProgram>` for HTMX-aware flows.

Example (trimmed):

```csharp
public class HtmxSmokeTests : IClassFixture<HtmxTestFixture<Program>>
{
	private readonly HtmxTestClient<Program> _client;
	public HtmxSmokeTests(HtmxTestFixture<Program> fixture) => _client = fixture.Client;

	[Fact]
	public async Task Todo_Htmx_Flow_Adds_And_Shows_Item()
	{
		var list = await _client.HtmxGetAsync("/Home/TodoList");
		list.AssertSuccess();
		await list.AssertPartialViewAsync();

		var added = await _client.HtmxPostAsync("/Home/AddTodo", new Dictionary<string,string>
		{
			["title"] = "HTMX integration test"
		});
		added.AssertSuccess();

		var listAfter = await _client.HtmxGetAsync("/Home/TodoList");
		await listAfter.AssertContainsAsync("HTMX integration test");
	}
}
```

Docs: /docs/features/testing-framework

Run tests:

```bash
dotnet test
```

## Docker

From `src/Web`:

```bash
docker build -t {{ProjectNameLower}}-web -f Dockerfile ..
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml up --build
```

Notes:
- Dockerfile builds/publishes Web with static assets and references Application/Infrastructure/Domain
- Auto-migrations run on Development startup
- DataProtection keys are configured for container session state

